title: Synth Buttons
description: Mordecai and Rigby realize that the bridge of the ship is also a synthesizer.

title: Time Loop
description: Mordecai and Rigby get stuck in a space-time loop.

title: Steak Me Amadeus
description: Mordecai wants to ask Margaret to be his girlfriend.

title: Sick Day
description: Mordecai and Rigby call in sick to work so they can ride on an epic water slide.

title: Robot Rap Battle
description: Mordecai and Rigby have a rap battle with robots.

title: Every Meat Burritos
description: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man and Fives want Every Meat Burritos from the Jimbros' Burritos drive-thru.

title: The Christmas Special
description: Mordecai and Rigby have to destroy a gift for Santa to save Christmas.

title: Party Re-Pete
description: Mordecai and Rigby have to save Benson from an evil party company.

title: Merry Christmas Mordecai
description: Mordecai has to get through a Christmas party with C.J. without messing everything up.

title: OOOHH!!!
description: Mordecai and Rigby tour the world dong their Ooohh celebration.

title: K.I.L.I.T. Radio
description: Muscle Man wants a local radio station to play the song he wrote for Starla.

title: Fries Night
description: Benson wants some french fries to overcome his depression.

title: Break Time
description: Benson breakdances during a work break.

title: Fun Run
description: Pops goes on a fun run across the country.

title: Christmas in Space
description: The guys celebrate their first Christmas in space by opening presents, eating peppermint bark and telling Christmas stories. Benson wants the stories to be more Christmas-y but the guys keep adding scary elements, which only infuriate their boss.

title: The Thanksgiving Special
description: The park guys need to get Thanksgiving dinner for their families to save Thanksgiving.

title: New Year's Kiss
description: Rigby has to stop Mordecai from kissing a girl on New Year's Eve.

title: 2001: A Nap Odyssey
description: The guys take a nap in zero gravity.

title: Pie Contest
description: Mordecai and Rigby want to prove to Benson that they can be judges at the pie contest.

title: This is My Jam
description: Rigby gets a terrible, terrible song stuck in his head and will go to any lengths to get it out.

title: Pizza Pouch Drop
description: Mordecai and Rigby risk their lives to cook pizza pouches evenly on all sides.

title: Snow Tubing
description: Rigby wants Eileen to go snow tubing.

title: Space Worm
description: Mordecai and Rigby ride a needy space worm.

title: Rigby in the Sky with Burrito
description: Rigby wants to accomplish at least one thing he said he would accomplish before his High School reunion.

title: Caveman
description: Mordecai and Rigby want to civilize a caveman so that Benson will let him stay at the park.

title: Last Meal
description: Muscle Man wants to eat his favorite foods before going on a diet.

title: Chili Cook-Off
description: Benson wants to get some street cred with the Park Managers' Association and win the big chili cook-off.

title: White Elephant Gift Exchange
description: The park guys want revenge on Muscle Man for all his terrible gifts.

title: Pilot
description: When two best friends, a blue jay named Mordecai and a raccoon named Rigby, play a game of rock, paper, scissors over a couch, it leads to dangerous results.

title: Coming Soon
description: Mordecai and Rigby find a voice modulator that makes them sound like a movie preview voiceover guy.

title: Ninja Shoes
description: Mordecai and Rigby try to sneak out of the house wearing ninja shoes.

title: The 1973 Tetherball Championship Trophy
description: Mordecai and Rigby compete to win a vintage tetherball championship trophy.

title: The Best Burger in the World
description: Mordecai and Rigby have to finish their chores before they can have burgers.
